\title{cleaving of a displayed category}
\date{2023-03-11T10:56:48+01:00}
\taxon{definition}
\author{jonmsterling}

\import{base-macros}
\import{frct-0000}


\p{Let #{E} be a [displayed category](frct-0000) over #{C}; following [Ahrens and Lumsdaine](ahrens-lumsdaine-2019), we define a \em{cleaving} of #{E} to be a function assigning to each #{\Mor{f}{x}{y}\in C}  and #{u\in C_y} a [cartesian morphism](frct-0001) #{\DispMor{\bar{f}}{f}{\InvImg{f}u}{u}} in #{E} called the \em{chosen cartesian lift} of #{u} along #{f}.}